                            <comment id="321332" author="lixi_wc" created="Wed, 22 Dec 2021 01:31:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on master. &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/fbe509c9-e6eb-40e7-a261-fb55d14a8b68&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/fbe509c9-e6eb-40e7-a261-fb55d14a8b68&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="253877" author="adilger" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2019 21:57:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems likely that this is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11933&quot; title=&quot;sanity-hsm: test_406 sanity: test_230b osd_declare_dir_delete() ASSERTION( dt_object_exists(dt) )&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11933&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11933&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which is an LASSERT() on the MDS during migration because the object is missing.  I suspect some kind of race condition, and where the &lt;tt&gt;-ENOENT&lt;/tt&gt; is seen decides whether the test just fails with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;no such file or directory&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; or triggers &quot;&lt;tt&gt;osd_declare_dir_delete() ASSERTION(dt_object_exists(dt))&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
